config files only accept spaces between between option flags and valuesâ€”CodeQL will throw an error if you use = to specify an option value.
If you specify an option in the command line, this overrides the config value defined for that option.
If you want to specify more than one option for a <command>, <subcommand> or globally, use one line per option.name: Label issue
on:
  issues:
    types: [opened]

jobs:
  label:
    name: Label issue
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    if: github.event.action == 'opened'
    steps:
      - name: Label issue
        env:
          GITHUB_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
        run: |
          echo '{"labels": ["CLI"]}' | gh api repos/${{ github.repository }}/issues/${{ github.event.issue.number }}/labels --input -
